{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218/events","html_url":"https://github.com/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218","id":2483532721,"node_id":"I_kwDOCykpn86UB7Ox","number":4218,"title":"[Feat] Add JSON output for columns in v.info","user":{"login":"wenzeslaus","id":5449060,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU0NDkwNjA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5449060?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus","html_url":"https://github.com/wenzeslaus","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wenzeslaus/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":1366106261,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMzY2MTA2MjYx","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"a2eeef","default":true,"description":"New feature or request"},{"id":1366106263,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMzY2MTA2MjYz","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/labels/good%20first%20issue","name":"good first issue","color":"7057ff","default":true,"description":"Good for newcomers"},{"id":3347189560,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwzMzQ3MTg5NTYw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/labels/C","name":"C","color":"7ED903","default":false,"description":"Related code is in C"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2024-08-23T17:02:58Z","updated_at":"2024-10-24T18:39:07Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**

The use of _c_ flag for _v.info_ should produce JSON with `format=json`:

```bash
grass --tmp-mapset ~/grassdata/nc_spm_08_grass7/ --exec v.info roadsmajor format=json -c
```

**Describe the solution you'd like**

JSON output which contains column names and metadata for these columns. Type is already in the current output, but there is more what could be included: other types of types (e.g., C versus SQL: [db_sqltype_to_Ctype](https://grass.osgeo.org/programming8/sqlCtype_8c.html#a1c02fe09d3c3d7632e4498494f3a1efc)) or some info on whether the column represents a number or whether it needs to be quoted in SQL (e.g., #1110).

**Describe alternatives you've considered**

The output could be a dictionary (mapping) or a list. In any case, the format should be extensible so more info can be included in the future. If a single column is a dictionary, then there is no problem with extending that. The question is if the list of columns should be in a dictionary.

Taking route of maximum flexibility:

```json
{
  "columns": [
    {
      "name": "cat",
      "sql_type": "INTEGER",
    },
    {
      "name": "MAJORRDS_",
      "sql_type": "DOUBLE PRECISION",
    }
  ]
}
```

Flexible only for the individual columns (simpler, but (perhaps?) less common list as a first level):

```json
[
  {
    "name": "cat",
    "sql_type": "INTEGER",
  },
  {
    "name": "MAJORRDS_",
    "sql_type": "DOUBLE PRECISION",
  }
]
```

Shortest possible:

```json
[
  {
    "name": "cat",
    "type": "INTEGER",
  },
  {
    "name": "MAJORRDS_",
    "type": "DOUBLE PRECISION",
  }
]
```

I don't think we should do this:

```json
{
  "names": ["cat", "MAJORRDS_"],
  "types": ["INTEGER", "DOUBLE PRECISION"]
}
```

**Additional context**

The output should be similar, compatible and/or in sync with _v.db.select_:

```sh
$ grass --tmp-mapset ~/grassdata/nc_spm_08_grass7/ --exec v.db.select roadsmajor format=json | jq .info
```

```json
{
  "columns": [
    {
      "name": "cat",
      "sql_type": "INTEGER",
      "is_number": true
    },
    {
      "name": "MAJORRDS_",
      "sql_type": "DOUBLE PRECISION",
      "is_number": true
    },
    {
      "name": "ROAD_NAME",
      "sql_type": "CHARACTER",
      "is_number": false
    },
    {
      "name": "MULTILANE",
      "sql_type": "CHARACTER",
      "is_number": false
    },
    {
      "name": "PROPYEAR",
      "sql_type": "INTEGER",
      "is_number": true
    },
    {
      "name": "OBJECTID",
      "sql_type": "INTEGER",
      "is_number": true
    },
    {
      "name": "SHAPE_LEN",
      "sql_type": "DOUBLE PRECISION",
      "is_number": true
    }
  ]
}
```

Currently, the following is produced with the _c_ flag:

```
Displaying column types/names for database connection of layer <1>:
INTEGER|cat
DOUBLE PRECISION|MAJORRDS_
CHARACTER|ROAD_NAME
CHARACTER|MULTILANE
INTEGER|PROPYEAR
INTEGER|OBJECTID
DOUBLE PRECISION|SHAPE_LEN
```

(The `Displaying column ...` text goes to stderr and should not be produced for JSON.)

We do have tools which give lists, e.g., `g.gisenv get="GISDBASE,LOCATION_NAME,MAPSET" sep="comma"`, but once the output is more complex, list on the first level seems too limiting - I included also info about the columns to _v.db.select_ so that the full information about the type is preserved and can be used to, e.g., create a derived table.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/comments/2436094991","html_url":"https://github.com/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218#issuecomment-2436094991","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/OSGeo/grass/issues/4218","id":2436094991,"node_id":"IC_kwDOCykpn86RM9wP","user":{"login":"NishantBansal2003","id":103022832,"node_id":"U_kgDOBiQA8A","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/103022832?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003","html_url":"https://github.com/NishantBansal2003","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NishantBansal2003/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"202